\begin_layout Section
Picking fancy colours
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As explained in the introductory course,
 \SpecialChar LaTeX
 has by default defined 21 colours you can use.
 A lot more colours are available via the 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "xcolor package"
target "https://ctan.org/pkg/xcolor"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 This package gives you three options,
 which unlock more and more different colours,
 in ascending order:
 dvipsnames,
 svgnames and x11name.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\SpecialChar LyX
 loads the xcolor package by default for every new document you create,
 but restricts colours to the basic ones unless instructed other.
 In the same field where you have already added 
\begin_inset Quotes xld
\end_inset

most
\begin_inset Quotes xrd
\end_inset

 in the preceding step,
 add a comma and then 
\series bold
either
\series default
 
\begin_inset Quotes xld
\end_inset

dvipsnames
\begin_inset Quotes xrd
\end_inset

 
\series bold
or
\series default
 
\begin_inset Quotes xld
\end_inset

svgnames
\begin_inset Quotes xrd
\end_inset

 
\series bold
or
\series default
 
\begin_inset Quotes xld
\end_inset

x11names
\begin_inset Quotes xrd
\end_inset

.
